This paper focuses on web security in shared hosting environments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the influence of hosting providers on the security practices of their customers, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The statistical analysis used in the paper falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computation and language (cs.CC).
